Title: The Long Road Home
Credit: Written by
Author: Edwon
Draft date: 2026-06-26

INT. NAKA'S APARTMENT - NIGHT

A cramped one-room flat. Rain streaks the window. NAKA (30s, tired)
stares at a cold cup of coffee.

NAKA
We can't keep doing this.

KENJI (O.S.)
Then let's stop.

EXT. CITY BORDER VIEWPOINT - DAWN

The skyline of YAMAMOTO glows pink. NAKA stands at the railing,
looking out over the valley.

NAKA
(quietly)
This is where it started.

She pulls a crumpled photo from her coat.

EXT. NEARBY ROADS - CONTINUOUS

A narrow road winds along the ridge. Power lines cut across the
grey morning sky. A single car passes.

KENJI
You drove all this way just to look at a road?

NAKA
It's not just a road.

CUT TO:

INT. TRAIN CROSSING SIGNAL BOX - DAY

Old switches and dusty manuals. KENJI flips a lever. Bells ring
somewhere far off.

KENJI
Everything still works. After all this time.

FADE OUT.
